<br>
Buffing:<br>
I don't mind being asked for an occasional sow, regen, sln, what have you, every now and again, but if you want it, you come to me.  No, I'm not going to run all around the zone looking for you (I hate that, esp when they're running around too), I'll tell you where I am, and you come to me.  If you take too long getting to me and I have better things to do with my time, or you go LD or get eatten by rabid kobalds or whatnot, don't complain to me if I don't wait half an hour for you.  Also, don't ask me to DS you every five minutes... I realize that buff doesn't last that long, but I wont sit and hold your hand (and in a sense PL you) just to refresh your DS every couple of minutes.  <br>
<br>
Porting:<br>
First and foremost, if you see me sitting naked outside the Seb orb (where I am bound atm), do not ask me for a port.  Most likely, the group or raid I was in is on a CR, and if I miss a rezz while I'm zoning, well, that's not going to make me very happy.  Other than that the rules for buffing apply here as well: You come to me if you want a port... that means, don't ask me to port you from another zone.  This has happened more than once, and I only did it once because I was in a particularly good mood, but when I went to pick up the guy, he was inspecting me (I don't have a problem with it, and I have the message turned off) but was asking if I had anything for sale.  I'm thinking, &quot;Okay, I come all the way out here to port you and you want to buy the armor off my back!?&quot;  And another time I was sitting in LS and someone sends me a tell asking for a port.  I stood up, looked around and didn't see anyone.  Out of habit, I did a /who all soandso.  The guy was /role or /anon, so I did /who soandso... nope, didn't turn up in the zone.  So I asked him where he was, and he said he was in WC... hmmmmmmmmmm, well then find a druid/wizzy in WC to give you a port.  <br>
<br>
*shakes her head*  <br>
<br>
And on top of everything else, yes, offer a donation, or AT LEAST, say thank you.  Not only the porting/buffing druids and rezzing clerics appreciate thanks and donations, but also the shammies who buff, the necros/sk who locate/summon your carcass (and necros can rezz), the pallies who rezz, the warriors who can taunt a mob off you to save your life, the monk and rogue who can deal out the last damage and kill what's about to kill you, the chanters who clarity/gom/insight et cetera, the bard who is the jack of all trades, the mage who is the walking Wal-Mart and summons you everything from bandaids to mod rods, the ranger who will track a mob for you, and the wizzies who port too, all appreciate it when you thank them (I hope I didn't forget anyone).  To the newbies/lowbies/pre-40's... when you are older you will understand why we rant about this, and perhaps you will then have a greater appreciation for our services.  Until then, take our advice and don't piss anyone off <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31224"><img src="http://www.angelfire.com/grrl/ithis/cass_signature.gif" border=0></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwolfypaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolfypaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ally Poster</span><br>  Posts: 624<br> <font color=#778899>(11/28/01 12:01:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Buff Beggers: A new twist</span><hr size=1> I like Tabbran's solution -- summon some throwing daggers.<br>
